  "technologyAgricultureDescription": "Opens the basic growth path. Farms and river farms let population grow faster and stabilize the first city.",
  "technologyWoodworkingDescription": "Develops the production side of mining. Lumber mills turn forests into production without going deep into metallurgy.",
  "technologyMiningDescription": "Opens the path of industry and infrastructure. Mines are the first major jump in city production.",
  "technologyAnimalHusbandryDescription": "Strengthens growth through animal resources. Pastures build a food economy and prepare the way to horseback riding.",
  "technologyHuntingDescription": "Opens the military and exploration branch. Provides camps and the first ranged unit for city production.",
  "technologyFishingDescription": "Develops cities near water. Fishing boats help coastal cities grow faster and prepare the way to the port.",
  "technologyCraftsmanshipDescription": "The first city production upgrade. The workshop keeps later buildings and units from blocking the queue too long.",
  "technologyTradeDescription": "The first step in the gold economy. The merchant hall gives a city a simple financial payoff after choosing a growth branch.",
  "technologyStorageDescription": "Stabilizes city growth. Storage helps maintain food pace and reduces the risk of development stalls.",
  "technologyWaterEngineeringDescription": "Expands the water growth path. The water mill rewards cities that control rivers.",
  "technologyStoneworkingDescription": "Combines production and defense. Quarries and the stonemason strengthen cities in the infrastructure branch.",
  "technologyMilitaryOrganizationDescription": "Builds the first military core of a city. Barracks strengthen production and defense before later army bonuses appear.",
  "technologyAdvancedTradeDescription": "Develops the economy after trade. The marketplace is a stronger gold building and prepares the path to banking.",
  "technologyConstructionDescription": "Expands territory and city maturity. Housing increases tile control and leads to administration and engineering.",
  "technologyNavigationDescription": "Opens a city payoff for the coast. The port requires coast/ocean access and rewards waterfront cities with food and gold.",
  "technologyIrrigationDescription": "Specializes water-based growth. The aqueduct grants a strong food bonus and additional territorial control.",
  "technologyBankingDescription": "Specializes the trade branch. The bank turns earlier markets into strong city income and unlocks the wider economy.",
  "technologyEngineeringDescription": "Construction specialization. The builders guild speeds production and increases the controlled tile limit.",
  "technologyMetallurgyDescription": "A strong industrial payoff after stoneworking. The forge raises production and prepares the path to iron and coal.",
  "technologyHorsebackRidingDescription": "A technology linking growth and war. The stable supports cities that invested earlier in animals and hunting.",
  "technologyIronWorkingDescription": "An industrial resource effect. Each controlled iron resource increases city production.",
  "technologyCoalMiningDescription": "A later industrial resource effect. Controlled coal increases city production and supports the factory path.",
  "technologyMachineryDescription": "A late infrastructure payoff. The factory gives a large production increase to cities that entered engineering.",
  "technologyAdministrationDescription": "Links infrastructure with economy. Town halls and monuments strengthen mature cities and lead to urbanization.",
  "technologyLogisticsDescription": "Speeds unit production. This is the main technology for players who want to field armies from cities more often.",
  "technologyShipbuildingDescription": "Develops the coastal/exploration subbranch. The lighthouse requires coast access and strengthens waterfront cities.",
  "technologyTacticsDescription": "Military city specialization. Training grounds add defense and production for military centers.",
  "technologyEconomyDescription": "A systemic payoff for banking. Increases gold generated by city economies.",
  "technologyUrbanizationDescription": "The final direction for large-city growth. Increases the population limit once the population system starts using hard caps.",
  "technologyFortificationsDescription": "Strengthens city defense. Grants a defensive bonus to the city economy, with its full meaning growing after combat and siege expansion.",
  "technologyStrategyDescription": "The final military direction. Strengthens army effectiveness as a late-game payoff after logistics.",
  "technologySpecializationDescription": "The final civic/economy payoff. Unlocks city specializations, adds city science, and helps finish late technologies in longer matches.",
  "technologyWritingDescription": "The first step toward science, law, and administration. The archive gives a city a permanent research base.",
  "technologyMathematicsDescription": "Connects science with territorial planning. The surveyor office helps cities control borders more effectively.",
  "technologyMedicineDescription": "Develops health and long-term growth in large cities through apothecaries, baths, and hospitals.",
  "technologyCivilServiceDescription": "Improves management of a large empire and unlocks courts that stabilize cities.",
  "technologySiegecraftDescription": "Opens siege warfare. Catapults and siege workshops break fortress cities.",
  "technologyCartographyDescription": "Develops exploration, maps, and the coast. Grants the map room and the first scout ships.",
  "technologyGuildsDescription": "Gives production cities a stage between the workshop and industry.",
  "technologyLawDescription": "Introduces order, policies, and civilian governance through courts.",
  "technologyEducationDescription": "Builds the full science path for cities through academies and universities.",
  "technologyUrbanPlanningDescription": "Develops great cities and territorial control through spatial planning.",
  "technologyNavalDoctrineDescription": "Turns ports into centers of fleets, shipyards, and force projection at sea.",
  "technologySteelDescription": "Introduces heavy industry and heavy infantry for the later front.",
  "technologyBureaucracyDescription": "Provides a major civic goal after administration: offices, ministries, museums, and parliament.",
  "technologyNationalismDescription": "Combines border defense, mobilization, and empire identity.",
  "technologyScientificMethodDescription": "Prepares late science, laboratories, observatories, and technology projects.",
  "technologySteamPowerDescription": "Opens rail, heavier logistics, and steam industry.",
  "technologyElectricityDescription": "Introduces power, infrastructure, and information reach.",
  "technologyCombustionDescription": "Gives oil importance and unlocks modern frontline units.",
  "technologyFlightDescription": "Introduces aviation, reconnaissance, and force projection over the front.",
  "technologyMassProductionDescription": "Develops final industrial production, tanks, and assembly plants.",
  "technologyRadioDescription": "Strengthens empire communication, visibility, and influence through broadcast towers.",
  "technologyNuclearPhysicsDescription": "Opens the reactor, uranium, and late endgame projects.",
